  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf edit a pinned message in a community channel and open the \"Pinned messages\" screen, the previous version of the message is displayed until the community is reopened.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/127517184-305ebfcb-ddab-40c3-9708-f07b9a2c97f5.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Create a community\r\n2. Send a message \r\n3. Pin the message\r\n4. Edit the message\r\n5. Open \"Pinned Messages\" (currently three dots at the top right > Pinned messages)\r\n6. Tap back to navigate to Home screen\r\n7. Open the community > Pinned messages\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 20/07\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
